<div class="heads blue">
    <h3>What’s this special bet of the day? And how to use it right?</h3>
</div>

<div class="callout">

    <p>Accumulator bet - this is a special type of bet that involves guessing several events at the same time. It differs in that the outcome coefficients are multiplied among themselves, which allows you to win an impressive amount.</p>
    <p>An example: if we take 3 Sport games</p>

    <table>
        <tr>
            <td>Squad A - Squad B</td>
            <td>bet on victory 2 (W2)</td>
            <td>odds 2.90</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Squad C - Squad D</td>
            <td>bet on victory 1 (W1)</td>
            <td>odds 1.40</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>Squad E - Squad F</td>
            <td>bet on victory 2 (W2)</td>
            <td>odds 2.42</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <p>Then all three Coefficients are multiplied among themselves (2.80 * 1.40 * 2.42) and the amount factor of 9.825 is nearly 10.</p>
    <p>So, if you make a bet with 20$, you may already win 200$, which is 10 times more than the initial bet.</p>
    <p>But here is only one drawback - you are gonna forfeit all the money if even one bet turns out to be wrong. Losing any choice means losing the entire bet.
    </p>

</div>

<div class="heads green">
    <h2>How to do it right on 1xbet?</h2>
</div>

<div class="callout">

    <p>If you are registered, and you have 1xbet download, you need to go into the app and choose the events that you want to add to your Accumulator.</p>
    <p>You can pick the event you are interested in the search bar. For instance, select <b>Milan - Liverpool, press W2</b>. Next click "<b>Add to bet slip</b>". You receive a notification that an event has been added.</p>

